{% set readingPosts = collections.posts | withAnyTagSlugs("books,now-reading") %}
{% set readingPost = readingPosts[0] %}

<article class="content content-page h-entry">
  <header class="post-header">
    <h1 class="section-title p-name">About</h1>
    <nav class="about-social" aria-label="Social links">
      <a class="about-social-link" href="/@bryan" aria-label="Mastodon">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-mastodon" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="https://bsky.app/profile/afterword.blog" aria-label="Bluesky">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-bluesky" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="{{ site.microblogUrl }}" aria-label="Micro.blog">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-microblog" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="/contact/" aria-label="Contact by email">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section class="post-full-content">
    <div class="content-body e-content">
      <p>Hello, fellow wanderer. I’m Bryan and this is my blog, a place where I write short updates about what’s going on in my life, post photos, and occasionally shout into the void.</p>

      <p>Some bloggers publish under their own name, treating a website almost like a digital stand in for themselves. I’ve always thought about this space a little differently. A person is a living thing that keeps changing, while a website is just a place to collect words. The name Afterword comes from the idea that life is the story and this blog is where a few reflections land afterward.</p>

      <p>I’m an urban planner by profession, having worked in long range planning, community development, and campus planning for nearly two decades. For better or worse, I spend a lot of time thinking about environmental psychology, urban design, landscape architecture, human geography, and public transportation. If those topics interest you, I also write about urbanism and related things <a href="https://lowvelocity.org">here</a>.</p>

      <p>Growing up in poverty shaped how I see the world. It left me with a deep belief that housing and healthcare are basic rights, and that education and a healthy environment should not depend on circumstance. I try to put that into practice by volunteering my time with causes that reflect those values.</p>

      <p>At my core, I enjoy creating. Writing, making music, practicing photography, gardening, cooking, learning web development, and improving our home are all ways I like to make things and understand the world a little better.</p>

      <p>Originally from the Great Lakes region, I have called the Pacific Northwest home for nearly ten years now. I am fiercely proud of my Midwest roots and sometimes suffer intense pangs of nostalgia and longings to return, especially after doom scrolling Zillow listings for a while.</p>

      <p>That said, I do love the climate and landscapes here on the West Coast. I enjoy getting outdoors with my young family, so you will find a lot of photos of our adventures scattered throughout the site.</p>

      <p>I love science fiction movies but have a terrible memory for titles and actors, so do not ask me which ones I have seen. I also enjoy geeking out about guitar gear and recently built my own Telecaster. You can see what I have been listening to lately <a href="/tags/listening/">here</a> or browse my growing <a href="/live-music-journal/">chronology of live music</a>.</p>

      <p>In 2020 I became an Italian citizen. What started as a genealogy hobby turned into a decade long education in Italian bureaucracy. My wife and I sometimes daydream about a part time life abroad, so I am always happy to connect with Italians and expats.</p>

      <p>You can reach me by <a href="/contact/">email</a>, follow my <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>, find me on <a href="/@bryan">Mastodon</a> or <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/afterword.blog">Bluesky</a>, or read my urbanism writing at <a href="https://lowvelocity.org">Low Velocity</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {% if readingPost %}
  <section class="section-block">
    <h2 class="section-title">Reading</h2>
    <div class="home-stream">
      {% set post = readingPost %}
      {% set streamImage = post | firstImage %}
      <article class="home-stream-item home-stream-item-reading h-entry">
        <p class="home-stream-meta home-stream-meta-reading">
          <a class="u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">
            <time class="dt-published" datetime="{{ post.published_at | htmlDateString }}">{{ post.published_at | dateDisplay }}</time>
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="home-stream-title-reading">
          <a class="p-name u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">{{ post.title }}</a>
        </p>
        {% if streamImage %}
          <a class="home-stream-media home-stream-media-reading u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">
            <img class="home-stream-image home-stream-image-listening u-photo" src="{{ streamImage.src }}" alt="{{ streamImage.alt }}" loading="lazy">
          </a>
        {% endif %}
        <div class="home-stream-body home-stream-body-reading e-content">
          {% if post.excerpt %}
            <p>{{ post.excerpt }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="listening-note">
      See all reading posts <a href="/books/">here</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
  {% endif %}
</article>
